    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>School or style of woodblock printmaking named for the Japanese port city. It offered glimpses of the customs and appearances of recently arrived visitors and large foreign resident population, usually produced for a Western audience.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
